place_description:
Wake is an exclusive, yet inclusive Coffee & Champagne Bar. Specialty drinks and cocktails are served with style and finesse. Whether you're here for an intimate date or with a group of friends our staff will serve you with hospitality and excellence, The Wake Way.
Our staff is well qualified in the techniques and quality ingredients used to create our crafted drinks; coffee and cocktails. Enjoy an afternoon or evening of charcuterie, high end pastries with your choice of coffee, champagne, wine, or beer.
Our vision was to create an exclusive experience for our community through hospitality while highlighting Charlotte's hidden gem, Mtn. Island Lake.

*Please Check our Instagram for the latest updates regarding liquor, alcohol.

reviews_data.review_text:
Very cute local business!!

Loved the aesthetic and the atmosphere of the shop! "Very cutesy, very mindful, very demure" lol!!!

Nice quality ingredient's

Tasty drinks.

I got the iced honey bee latte and my daughter got a boba tea.

Overall reasonable price point.
Perfect shop for great coffee - which is much better than the other place. Unique in its decor and atmosphere. Will definitely be a return customer.
Best and cutest coffee shop in Charlotte. Creme brulee late and honey bee latte are sooooo good.
I've been a few times and the coffee is amazing, atmosphere is wonderful and staff is friendly.

Excellent place to have coffee or some other drinks. The place is comfortable, and the ambiance is just perfect for some hot chocolate or coffee in the morning. The place is comfortable and quiet, a perfect setting to do some work in the morning or to meet other people. The hot chocolate of this place is excellent, and the price is very good.

The parking space is spacious and excellent. The location is close to Mountain Island, Stonewater, and the Overlook neighborhood. The place is very accessible. The restroom is very clean and well maintained.

The place also offers outdoor seating. Overall an excellent place!

This is such a unique little coffee shop! You can rent a room that can fit around 4-5 people, and then you have two little areas for one person if you want to work on your laptop. Recommend 10 out of 10!

I'm the kind of person that researches menus before going places because I want to know that I have options that support my dietary preferences. I was so pleased to see that Wake Coffee offer Golden Milk with local honey and the option of milk alternatives. I ordered it with almond milk and it was absolutely delicious. You can taste the turmeric and cinnamon and see the sediment of the ingredients at the bottom of the cup; a sign that they use actual dried ingredients and not just flavored syrups.

They also let me use my reusable cup which makes me happy. The shop was playing all the 90s/2000s throw back jams when I visited. It's clean, comfortable and has multiple seating areas. There is outdoor seating as well. Lots of drink options that don't involve coffee which is a plus. Service was super friendly. Parking is very accessible and easy.
I ordered a golden latte and it was disgusting. I can't even explain how bad it was. I seriously suggest the management to train the baristas on how to make lattes

I visited Wake Coffee to do a little work and I'm so glad I did. I was greeted pleasantly and I ordered a large "stress no more herbal tea" from the very helpful staff that helped me narrow down my beverage options. I walked back to my reserved focus room area and was able to be productive as I worked and sipped on my delicious tea in the quiet atmosphere. The space is beautifully decorated and everyone I interacted with was super friendly and kind. I look forward to returning to Wake Coffee soon. Thank you!
So thankful for this sweet spot!
This is a great coffee shop/cocktail bar. I hosted an event and Amber was amazing. Charcuterie was lovely and my guests raved about the drinks. Immaculate vibes! Thank you so much Wake Coffee Co!
This is such a nice coffee spot, we found it by accident by looking online on Google. Great staff and coffee!
I love the coffee, and the quietness of the shop.

Super cute local coffee shop with fun events and pop ups. I love the fun menu even though my usual orders are simple. An iced chai with vanilla is my favorite and a drip coffee with a pump of chocolate and caramel sauce is so good, their coffee is so smooth and delicious.  Really glad to find a nearby coffee shop with quality coffee for a good price, and it's nice to chat with the friendly owners when they're in the shop.

LOVE this spot. The coffee is incredible. My order is always consistent unlike Dunkin' or Starbucks. You can taste the quality. The new hours have made it so much more convenient  especially on weekends. Support local!

Wake Coffee is a dream! From the beautiful aesthetic, to the amazing associates who work there and the smooth coffee and espresso, it's my go to coffee shop. I ditched the big cookie cutter corporate coffee companies for a great place like Wake. I can't wait to try them out in the evening for cocktails and charcuterie. This place really brings class to the Mt. Island Lake area.

Everytime I've come to wake I've always had a more than exceptional experience. The staff is kind and attentive, the drinks are yummy and creative, and it's the perfect environment for getting some work done!

My son wanted the 24 karat gold latte and when he got it he noticed it didn't have gold in it. When asked they said they have been out of gold for weeks! Why keep selling the latte then if the main ingredient is missing? They were nice enough to refund when asked where the gold was but it still didn't seem right that they didn't tell us before the purchase. Also it was a little too sweet.

I came on a Sunday because I wanted a good coffee and I was tired of going to the chain locations. I ordered from here on DoorDash but this was my first time visiting in person and I will say I didn't feel very welcomed and I was passed over in the line. I ordered a frozen mocha which I thought was pretty good. Over all I may visit again. The atmosphere there was really nice for you to come work at during the day or to even rent a space to work at for a while.
Literally THE best iced chai tea i've had in Charlotte. Atmosphere cute & classy, the staff friendly. Got to meet the owner, very welcoming! 10/10 for me

The coffee and space were amazing!! We went on a Sunday and we didn't have the best customer service experience. While the young lady working was nice, she seemed overwhelmed, took a long time with the simple order before us, and with our order as well.  Since this was our first time here and it could have just been an off day, we'll come back and try again in the future.
Loved this coffee shop. Tasty coffee, great service. Love supporting locals. Stop by and try it out.
The iced mocha is amazingly good! A found this place headed to a meeting at another coffee house cause I couldn't abide one more of theirs. So glad I did a quick stop here.
Great little place

I'm always in search of independent coffee shops because I feel like the intentions are often so pure. This place is exactly that.
In a deep pool Starbucks, they stand out the perfect gem  a great coffee shop with incredibly tasteful decor.
Bonus the coffee shop feels so comfortable that you just want to spend the day there. I spent a few hours there in an open space and then I reserved a quiet to host a virtual meeting.
I love that you have the freedom to reserve the quiet spaces away from the music and noise of the coffee shop. They even have a cute preservable meeting room that has a monitor & etc.
I appreciate that the Internet was very strong might be a silly thing to some, but often I find in public spaces it's hard to host meetings without connection issues.
I had a delicious iced chai with oat milk, then a glass of Prosecco. Did I mention that they have a full bar too?
This is the perfect spot to host any sort of group, gatherings, or meetups and because of the style of the place also perfect to capture clips or pics for social. The staff was very pleasant and engaging as well as the other patrons. The fun thing about places that have great energy is that they typically draw other people with equally great energy making it a really cozy environment.
Total Bonus-even the bathrooms are cute and clean!!
Thanks for being so intentional with this coffee shop! I don't live nearby, but I will be back anytime in the area
Phenomenal salted coffee
The owner is so sweet, and some of th best coffee I've ever had.
Cute, chic, clean, quiet, friendly and delicious iced oatmilk lattes. It offers study booths/rooms available for fee and I also noticed they have local art. I def recommend.

Ordered a drink off the seasonal menu: The Ube Matcha Latte (iced with whole milk). It was amazing. Great flavor, not too sweet. Perfect drink for this weather.
The staff were so kind and made my drink so fast I didn't even notice it was done!
The inside of the cafe was beautiful and seemed like a great place to just hang out for a while.
Will definitely be back next time I'm in town!
Fantastico lugar.. el cafe  sabroso atmosfera perfecta.
Best coffee in Charlotte. The place is so cute and the staff is super friendly! They have cocktails as well which is always a plus. 10/10
An absolute gem! Came here 3/3 mornings while visiting the area. The lattes are incredible and the pastries and bagels hit the spot. Can't wait to come back!
Very good cappuccino

Beautiful place, I loved the aesthetic & the coffee was amazing! I got the salted caramel iced latte it was 10/10! I went with 2 friends & we sat in the back reserved room, it was perfect to just hang out & talk for a bit & not disturb anyone else! Will definitely return soon :)

I was looking for another cafe option that wasn't Starbucks or Dunkin.

The location has plenty of parking.

There's only pastry options, but I love that they have macarons. I was curious about their wine and charcuterie though.

There's a variety of drink options and you're able to customize a drink with the products they have.

I ordered the Blue Matcha Iced. It's truly premium and not earthy tasting as regular matcha. I also had a custom order made for a friend.

Service was great! Super nice, friendly, answered all my questions!
Adorable little coffee shop! Comfortable seating, private study and meeting areas, friendly service, and good pastries! Coffee has a strong nutty flavor.
Owner was incredibly nice. She put a lot of care in effort in her drinks, and they were amazing.

Wonderful coffee so personal and friendly service by the actual owner . Something you don't see much these days , an owner that actually works and takes pride in  their own business and not just there to come in and collect the money. Starbucks could learn alot from Wake Coffee.

Awesome little gem!
Great environment and unique decor.
There's lots of seating options and seating areas- from the large table, to individual chairs, the bench, outside and the bar.
The have 3 more private areas if you need to get done with done and even a private room it says you can reserve (not sure on cost of that)
The latte I got was tasty, though it was night so I got decaf and it wasn't spectacular.
My wife got the Lavender Vanilla latte and said it's the best she's ever had (it was quite tasty!
It was very clean.

I recommend checking out this place.

My only complaint is the high cost of the drinks.

What an incredible place to have so close to Mount Holly! The coffee and cake pops are great! A must get drink is the frozen hot chocolate. I saw 2 other people get it before me and decided "why not?"  Tasted just like an espresso martini without the alcohol! This is a perfect location for parents dropping off their kids at Romp n' Roll or just hanging out and working or chatting. The owner was wonderful and so helpful with explaining all the different drinks to her customers. 5 stars all around!

Delicious coffee! The barista was so kind and worked the whole time my husband and I sat and enjoyed our coffee. When he wasn't making drinks, he stayed busy cleaning or doing other things around the shop. The owner is blessed to have such a hard worker that respects his job so much!
Will definitely be going back!

The kind barista allowed us to use a private, cozy room to accommodate our need for privacy. Very thoughtful and helpful. Pleasant experience.
There is also public tables and comfortable small tables for those just hanging out.
My first experience there. Live out of town. Unique flavors for hot espresso/coffee. I recommend
We enjoyed our stop. The golden milk latte was very good. We appreciated the explanation of the place and the menu when we walked in.

My favorite getaway for a delicious crafted coffee or a nice place to work! Ambers cocktails, catering, and coffee is one of kind and so delicious. Her charcuterie boards are a work of art. Her coffee is by far better than starbucks ! This place is also a boujee and top notch venue to host your intimate gathering or party . Makes for a beautiful backdrop for photo ops! The cutest coffee shop in town beautifully and thoughtfully designed in and out ! From coffee to setting its a total vibe at Wake with 5 star  customer service.
Amazing service, great interior, awesome owners, private office for zoom meetings, worker corners, couldn't ask for more.

I have been probably in 20 or more coffee shop in NC between Greensboro and Charlotte area and also a coffee knowledgeable person, having said that, I went to Wake Coffee yesterday and I was impressed with the barista,, please forgive me because I forgot her name, a very young lady that made me a Cappuccino very very good!!!! Excellent service, well presented and delicious. Also Met Tad, owner and we had a very nice chat. I'm highly recommend this place. Lastly, the place includes the bathroom was impeccable.

Absolutely obsessed with their coffee. Truly the best   latte I've ever had! The iced white chocolate latte is absolutely out of this world amazing. Great atmosphere and staff. Highly highly recommend.

This place has ruined espresso for us anywhere else. We try other places, and are always let down when we compare to this place. It has become our weekly addiction. Their iced latte is incredible. Absolutely love it. Highly recommend for anyone that wants real, good quality coffee. Can't wait to try the rest of the menu.
Lovely little coffee shop. First visit today. Service was quick and friendly and the salted caramel latte had delicious flavor. Will stop again when on this side of town.
First time there. Maria was great and my London fog latte was delicious!
Great relaxing atmosphere!! Amazing americano! (Work emails didn't seem as bad here) 10/10

Maria was so pleasant and helpful as I was ordering a sugar free coffee drink.  Both my daughter and I had questions and she went above and beyond to make us feel welcome.  My daughter was so impressed she asked to come back again tomorrow! My drink is delicious and the atmosphere is amazing.
Best cold brew in the area! My morning go to; always friendly and timely.

Kelsie was great as always!!! This shop is kinda tucked away from the main road, but more than worth the visit! Hands down the best White Chocolate Mocha ever, and every thing else I have tried is awesome! Atmosphere is very pleasing!
Good coffee I love all of their honey items
Cold brew had awful taste and lacked any coffee flavor; couldn't finish this drink. Iced caramel latte was overly sweet.

Met the Owner and she has such the sweetest personality! Customer service was great and so was the Pink Tiger Boba Tea we bought! Great location to chill out at with Wi-Fi and to just wine down with friends. Try this place out!

Owner is very friendly! Really enjoyed talking with her. The shop has a homie feel to it and the coffee is great! Got a large and had to come back as I let my Mom try it and split my large with her so I came back within 15 minutes for 2 smalls. Coffee definitely makes you do a happy dance with the taste! Will 100% be back for more and prices are very reasonable.
Really cool staff and great drinks!

Cute little spot with a variety of options!
They have coffee, boba, tea, cocktails and snacks!
Went to an event there with our foster dog, great people and service. My tea was delicious and made how I requested!
Coffee was good, very friendly people too
The "wake at the lake" is one of the best coffee drinks I've ever had if you like coconut/ pineapple flavored things take my advice and get it with oat milk :)
The vanilla latte was very sweet and not espresso-y at all. Like it didn't even taste like there was coffee in it. The macaron, though!!! *chefs kiss*

I just went to wick coffee for the first time today. Charming, modern coffeehouse, atmosphere, friendly, staff, and delicious options. I have been vegan for many years and they have incredible nondairy options on the menu. Today I tried creme brulee latte with oat milk, and it was outstanding! Definitely check them out.
What a cute place!!! You can get coffee or an evening drink and food to accommodate either occasion. Staff is friendly and polite.
Fantastic coffee, love the decor too!
Always love my order but the wait time is a little long. Sometimes it can be quick but I guess it depends on the time you come in. Morning definitely not a good choice.
This place is AMAZING! I got the lavender latte and it was great! The workspaces are super cool. I would highly recommend it! Come and grab a coffee but also just chill and relax!
Loved the vibe from this place, so many drinks to choose from & everything we got was delicious! Definitely coming back to try the whole menu.
I love this local coffee shop!!
This is the most beautiful and relaxing setup.
Great place with amazing coffee and drinks!

Their Honey Bee Latte is to die for. Space is so beautiful, great place for remote work as well as a cocktail after work. Very quick service as well.
They also have liquor, beer and wine, so a great place to stop in after work for happy hour or a date night!
Everything about this coffee shop is beautiful and delicious! :) Rich delicious drinks and the decor is stunning! Of course the staff are very kind and hospitable too. Very cozy, chic coffee shop :)

my new favorite coffee shop. I had the creme brulee latte with oat milk and it was amazing. They have other great seasonal flavors as well, and a ton of sugar free syrup options. The inside is cute and the layout is really good. I brought my laptop and worked here for a few hours, it's a really good atmosphere for that, quiet but still has music playing. They also have a small conference room and more quiet laptop spaces that you can reserve/rent.

Fantastic coffee and cocktails.

Great service.

Reasonably priced excellent coffee! The coffee beans are top notch and has real flavor profile. I ordered Americano without sugar and milk, and you can actually taste the flavor notes! Would recommend if you're at Mount Holly area. Much better than Starbucks.
The best little gem in Mountain Island, I drive past several other coffee shops to grab coffee at Wake!  Love the vibe, best espresso, and the all the baristas are sweet and friendly!
By far the best coffee in and around the Charlotte area with the friendliest staff!
Great coffee, great atmosphere, great people. Highly recommend!
Excellent atmosphere, great coffee, and the owner is super nice. Definitely a different vibe than the previous coffee shops that occupied this location. Let's support our local businesses

This place has been renovated exceptionally. They have a really fun drink menu for both coffee & wine/beer/seltzer etc. plus cute lil charcuterie boards. Service was amazing too. Can't wait to come back here

If you need a great remote work space to post up in and get some undistracted caffeine fueled work done in a chill spot with great vibes, look not further than @wakecoffeeco near Mountain Island Lake. Personally, I needed to chill out and focus more than I needed the caffeine, so I went with the No More Stress Tea, it worked great  de-stressed. Wake Coffee also has snacks, sweets pastries, and a selection of beer wine and liquor for cocktails. When you're done working, you can relax for a minute and enjoy an adult beverage with a tasty treat as a reward for your hard days work. Go check out Wake Coffee Co. Today!

Wake Coffee Co is awesome! They have a great location and the coffee is phenomenal. I tried the creme brulee latte and it was to die for! I also appreciate the local art they have on display. I definitely recommend this shop!
-Garreth Kelsey, REALTOR
The manager, Amber is so friendly and drinks were delicious! I would definitely come back all the time !
Stopped in to try a  house blend hot coffee. Serene and quiet atmosphere which is conducive for conversation. Nice selection of fare which includes  champagne, charcuterie, wine and beer.

This was ok, nothing special but like that it's local and would go here over starbucks or any big chain..
good place to plug in and work from if you have that need and the vibe definitely feels tuned to that demographic.
food and straight up coffee was ok but nothing special.
The staff are nice enough.
I get the sense this is a good place for cocktails and blended coffee drinks so if that's your thing this might be right up your alley.
Coffee and pastries are fabulous !!! It's decorated so nicely! Highly recommend
Very different Coffee and Wine Establishment. Beautiful design and atmosphere. Kelsey was extremely helpful and knowledgeable about their beverage offerings.
Beautiful facility, friendly staff and delicious coffee! Would highly recommend visiting Wake Coffee and grabbing a boba tea or the lavender vanilla latte  so yummy!
Incredible cup of coffee and great staff.
Had Mariah as my Barista, did a great job with my drink, was delish and was super friendly, will be back!

Visited here and was helped by the sweetest barista, Mariah. She suggested i try the lavender vanilla latte and it was definitely a great choice! Would recommend this place to all of my friends and family, such a cute spot. :)
Happened to come in here while waiting on a ride and it was a great decision. Really really good lattes and very friendly. Their Boba was great too!

Wake is our favorite coffee place. Amber, Kelsey, Mariah, and the rest of the guys are awesome. They really get to know you and remember what you like. Very comfortable seating and I always feel safe there.

First time stopping in for my husband and myself. It is such a nice place and the menu has such a wide variety of choices! Our drinks were delicious (Sugar Free Coconut Latte & Salted Caramel Latte). Met the owner who was super nice and personable. We will definitely be repeat customers!!

We enjoyed charcuterie board on a Friday night, which was so fun! There were some girls ordering some super fun colorful drinks and there were also work stations on the back.  This place has it all and is designed so nicely! 10/10 check it out.
We met friends for a charcuterie board that was amazingly delicious. Fantastic environment and great service.

When I say this place pulls out all of the stops, I truly mean it! The sweetest staff, each drink hand created and made into a work of art, and coffee that is top notch.
Oh and those snacks, so many great options! Great for a mid-morning pick me up or a date night with friends or a spouse.

Went for a decaf Americano but they do not offer decaf espresso at all. I was able to get a decaf iced coffee. But they don't offer hot decaf coffee. I'm on a dietary restriction that I cannot have caffeinated coffee so I cannot put this on my list. But the decaf iced coffee that I got was good. Nice atmosphere.
Great experience! Delightful service and amazing coffee drinks! Definitely coming back for an evening night out for cocktails and charcuterie!

Definitely delicious drinks. Starbucks prices but understandable they have to pay the rent. Great small space to grab a coffee and work from but don't be alarmed you have to pay for a membership fee for laptop spaces. Which I think is a little ridiculous because there is NEVER anyone in those spaces. Encourage more people to work from here and more sales will occur. They also have beer and wine!

STUNNING. Everything about Wake Coffee Co. is exactly that! The owners are truly passionate and it shows in the drinks they create all the way to the design of the bathroom (tiger wall paper? Yes, please!).

Our first time in was in the evening so we wanted to try their cocktails. Inventive and well executed we ordered the Orange Dreamsicle and the Dark and Stormy, both were refreshing and picturesque! They are very much a family-owned establishment and one of the owners made our drinks! The conversation and atmosphere will keep us going back!

The next morning we decided we needed to try their coffee to give a really in depth review. We both got the Honey Bee Latte but tried it iced and hot. Both were phenomenal! They also have boba tea on their menu which is so hard to find outside of the city! That's up next on my list of things to try.

They have areas you can set up your laptop and work from, an area for small meetings, comfortable couches, locally sourced wood tables, and some outdoor seating as well!

TLDR; Whether you just need a good drink or somewhere to get some work done during the week - give Wake Coffee Co a shot!

I discovered this gem searching randomly for "Coffee Shops Near Me" and wow, what a find. The atmosphere and staff made this a very pleasant experience, one that I plan to share with my wife for her birthday (she's looking forward to the charcuterie box and wine).

This is a great coffee shop, and our server Amber was awesome! They have everything from specialty espresso drinks to cold brew and boba tea. They have a good selection of baked goods to snack on. It's also a cute spot to get an adult beverage (they have wine, beer and cocktails). I definitely recommend this spot for either coffee and/or a drink after work.
First time and I'll be back! Next time I want to come back at night and try the cocktails. I had a sugar free white mocha and it was delicious! Well done!!

I like this place. The staff was very kind and friendly. The bathroom was incredible clean. All in the environment is perfect to study, to work, to meetings. The concept is great. I wish you the best guys. Please keep going that way.

After getting watery cold brew at another local coffee shop, we decided to try again at Wake Coffee Co. since we were on the road and desperate for good caffeine lol. Thank God! Wake Coffee Co. is amazing and we will be coming back if we're ever in the area again!

I love this place! The inside decor is unlike any other coffee shop I have been to; the staff are the best; and the drinks taste amazing. I recommend this place to anyone, especially for those who like to find a great place to work remote.
Coming here has become part of our daily routine because they have the best coffee in the area. Try them out and you'll taste what I'm talking about.
We love this place! My daughter and I had a special girls date. The drink options are amazing. I love the decor and the staff is very friendly. You must try it!

From the amazing blends of coffee, to the great wine bar, Wake Coffee Co. truly is an experience everyone should have!  The atmosphere is very warm and friendly and private rooms are an amazing addition to this beautiful coffee shop.  The owners and staff are very hospitable.  It is obvious from the time you walk in the door that they have a heart for serving.  My husband and I absolute love this place and will be back to visit again soon!

Couldn't ask for a better coffee shop + champagne bar. Neat concept. The owner is very sweet and friendly. The coffee is delicious! The environment is chic, inviting, and there's space to chat with a friend or to work. Wish we lived closer!
Wake is great! You can tell the owners take pride in everything they do. I recommend to friends as often as I can. Great spot and even greater owners. Inclusive and welcoming environment.
Great coffee and atmosphere, I never have to question the quality or service. Love the Honey Bee and how smooth the coffee is. They have a wonderful staff and it feels like home!

Not only is this one of the cutest coffee shops I've been to, but their coffee is seriously just as good. I've had a few different ones and I'm obsessed. Seriously get to Wake! Such a good environment for work, too. Study rooms and even a mini meeting room! Love it here.

Wake Coffee is an outstanding place to stop for a cup of coffee and other fun beverages.  They always have sweet cookies, macaroons, and even charcuteries!  This is a great place to meet up with friends or even a great spot to bring out of town guests.  The staff is always welcoming!  The ambiance and decor make it a fun place to stop for a quick cup of Joe or spend a little time gathering with friends!  Can't wait to go back!
Love Wake Coffe Co! This is not your typical coffee shop. It has so many fun drinks to go back and try! Although those pastries are  too! I can't get out of there without one!

Love Wake Coffee!!  Both hot and cold beverages, they've got you covered!  Everything I've had has been awesome, and don't forget to try the macaroons and boba beverages!    The atmosphere is upscale yet relaxed, and friendly. Such an excellent addition to our area!  A must try, you won't be disappointed!

Friendliest staff and the best coffee around! This is the best place to relax and study! And please do not miss their pastries.. they are to die for!
#wakecoffeeco

Wow, the drink I had was awesome! A specialty coffee recommended by the barista. Its rare you step into a place where people SMILE and actually care you are there. Aweome space,I met up with some friends,but I will for sure meet up with clients as well. Perfect space as a real estate agent to meet clients, or if you need a space to do work. Small private spaces are available and the location is easy. Keep doing what you guys are doing, nice people and nice space and perfect coffee makes ME want to return and spend my money!
Huge menu selection and great ambiance. A great place to set up shop and get some work done as they have a private meeting room as well as individual workspaces for those who work remotely.

I had the best sugar free Coconut latte ever! This coffee was delicious and will leave you wanting more! I enjoyed the environment and friendly staff. And the options of private little nooks. Wake Coffee also has scrumptious desserts from local bakeries ... delicious! Their menu offers what no other coffee company does in the way of specialty drinks. A very pleasant experience and I'll definitely be back for more.
Family owned small business. Quality coffee, other fun and exclusive options, super cool environment. This should be your regular coffee spot!
Great coffee and banana nut muffin. Brittany provided me with alot of information about the place and was awesome. I'm glad that I stopped by and will most definitely be back.
Very delicious coffee and awesome  customer service!!  Love to support local!
What an awesome experience!!  Such delicious coffee with lots of non dairy options!  Quick, easy, and great customer service also!!  Love supporting local!

Amazing coffee.  Clean and beautiful interior.  Friendly professional staff who make a rockin cup of yummy!  Shout out to Mackenzie (hopefully I spelled that right) as she was patient with our questions.  Will be going back.  Support local!!

I have been here a few times and everytime gets better. I've tried 4 differant drinks and all were delicious, my fav is the 24k gold latte it has actual gold flakes on the top. The staff and owners a really friendly and have put together a great coffee shop.
I like strong coffee, and Amber S. made a great latte with Italian Espresso, coconut milk, and Boba added.

First time in and Jessica was patient and answered all of my questions with no problem. Sign up is easy and cheap. $1 for a year. I got the Cold Brew and it's smooth and strong. Bold flavor. I'm a fan.
Brought my sister to Wake a few weeks ago and we loved it! My Honey Bee Latte was great! Amber S. was a great barista and super kind. Will come back again.

We came to this coffee shop last week on a roadtrip. When we went inside to get coffee, we were told that have to pay an extra $1 just to order coffee if you don't have a membership? Not the best business model. We ended up going to Starbucks across the street instead. Staff was kind & the place was well decorated which is why I bumped it up a star.

I have probably been in and out of 500 coffee shops all over the country over the past ten years.  So saying this is rare but this is a special place I love everything about it mainly it's different it's edgy and modern but at the same time comfortable with a welcoming staff that's not upselling you for extras the whole time. Very knowledgeable and just great people. I enjoyed the whole experience. The menu is great it's not obnoxiously big but it is diverse, eclectic, well thought out, and has both the classic option but also some really cool new drinks I haven't heard of I had a bubble tea I believe and it was spectacular. Aiden you were great thanks for all of the help!  You guys knocked this concept out of the park!!  Great job I will be back a lot
My first time visiting and it was one of the BEST lattes I've had! I got the Cupcake latte, and it tastes exactly like a cupcake! Will be returning soon.
Love this place! Great drinks and the owners are awesome! Will be back for sure!
Today was my first time at Wake Coffee, the barista was very kind and helpful. The coffee is actual coffee, not that watered down Dunkin coffee. 10/10 will be coming back!
The coffee and lattes are amazing! I've been there almost everyday since opening (I work near by). The staff is super friendly and the atmosphere is so welcoming!
Excellent coffee and service. Definitely will be back.
Fantastic coffee and great atmosphere! The rich sea salted caramel mocha coffee is excellent. Highly recommend this gem of a place!

My new favorite coffee shop! Great coffee, great snacks. They even have keto/paleo friendly options. I love that they have milk alternatives for those who have sensitives to dairy or may be vegan.
